        <p class="fs-5 text-secondary">July 22nd 2026 – August 9th 2026<br>Directed by Aaron Henrickson<br>Starring Amanda Egle and Taylor Adams</p>
        <p class="lead">
        A searing -- and, for better or worse, timeless -- comedy penned by English screenwriter and playwright Mike Bartlett, <a href="https://www.eventbrite.com/e/an-intervention-by-mike-bartlett-tickets-1991580937195" target="_black" rel="nofollow" class="link-dark">An Intervention</a> deftly and humorously explores a hairline fracture in a 3-year friendship that fissures into a vast canyon. The title is a sharp double-entendre: she needs an intervention for her drinking, while he supports an intervention… elsewhere.
        </p>
        <p class="lead">
        First produced in the UK in 2014, the script deploys quick-witted banter to enchant audiences and remains just challenging enough to spark engaging discussions for the ride home. Performed by two fresh and electrifying Chicago actors, what better way to bring friends and communities together than with something hilarious that speaks to the moment?
        </p>
